ce:section.ce:para:
Herein, a strong CL was obtained when a doped CDs (CDs-Cl,P) was added into the reaction of H2O2-KMnO4. The CDs-Cl,P were synthesized in a one-step hydrothermal process using sucrose, muriatic acid and phosphoric acid as precursors. Stronger CL occurred when Cu2+ was injected into the CDs-Cl,P-H2O2-KMnO4 system. Studies were conducted to investigate the properties and mechanism of the new CDs-Cl,P-H2O2-KMnO4-Cu2+ CL system in detail, in which CDs-Cl,P acted as catalyst and energy acceptor, and Cu2+ performed catalytic activity toward H2O2. TA possesses multiple o-diphenol groups and is therefore capable of forming chelates with many metal ions, including Cu2+ 
                     [31]. This led to a decrease of the CL intensity of the CDs-Cl,P-H2O2-KMnO4-Cu2+ system in the presence of TA with the decrease of the concentration of free Cu2+. Therefore, the CDs-Cl,P-H2O2-KMnO4 CL system could be used for the sensitive and selective determination of Cu2+ due to its enhancement and TA based on its inhibitory effect for the CDs-Cl,P-H2O2-KMnO4-Cu2+ system (Scheme 1
                     ).
